BY AFRICANEWS <img src="https://www.newsday.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/AL-bA.jpg" alt="" width="900" height="506" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3096224744018786" srcset="https://www.newsday.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/AL-bA.jpg 900w, https://www.newsday.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/AL-bA-300x169.jpg 300w, https://www.newsday.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/AL-bA-768x432.jpg 768w, https://www.newsday.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/AL-bA-30x17.jpg 30w" sizes="(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px" /> Ousted Sudanese president Omar al-Bashir has been transferred from a holding facility into jail, multiple reports have confirmed. He was forced out of power a little over a week ago by the military on the back of massive protests. The Transitional Military Council, TMC, confirmed his arrest days after his ouster. The Reuters news agency reports that he is being held in the capital Khartoum at the Kobar maximum security prison. They added that he is being held in solitary confinement under tight security.